The 73-year-old Hayward community leader died at the nursing home after a short battle with COVID-19.
Thirteen residents of the nursing home have died, and scores of patients and staff members have been infected.
Many knew Mitzman for his deep love of Disney, especially of Mickey Mouse.
But he was most known in the community for his service to students.
“He was the epitome of someone who was a champion for students,” Benson Stagg said.